Step-by-Step Guide: Recovering Deleted Files with Disk Drill
Step 1: Stop Using the Drive Immediately

Do not:

Copy new files to the drive
Move files onto the drive
Install software on the drive
Continue editing from the drive

The less you use the drive, the better your chances of recovery.

Step 2: Download Disk Drill

Download Disk Drill from:

https://www.cleverfiles.com/disk-drill-windows.html

Install it on a different drive than the one you are trying to recover.

For example:

✅ Install on your computer's internal SSD

❌ Do not install on the SSD that contains the deleted files

Step 3: Connect the Drive

Connect the SSD or hard drive containing the deleted files to your computer.

In my case, I connected my Samsung T7 1TB SSD to a Windows PC.

Step 4: Launch Disk Drill

Open Disk Drill.

You should see a list of all connected drives.

Locate the drive that contains the deleted files.

Step 5: Start the Scan

Click on the drive.

Click Search for Lost Data.

Disk Drill will begin scanning.

Depending on your drive size, this may take several hours.

My scan took approximately 4 to 5 hours.

Do not interrupt the process.

Step 6: Review Found Files

Once the scan is complete:

Click Review Found Items
Browse through folders
Preview files whenever possible
Search by file type if necessary

Take your time.

The files you're looking for may not be in the first folder you open.

Step 7: Recover the Files

Select the files you want to recover.

Click Recover.

IMPORTANT:

Choose a different drive as the destination.

Example:

✅ Recover to your computer's internal SSD

❌ Do not recover back to the same SSD

This prevents overwriting additional recoverable data.

Step 8: Verify Everything

Open all important files.

Some files may work perfectly.

Others may be corrupted.

This is exactly what happened in my case.

Many clips opened immediately, but some larger video files would not play.

The Next Problem: Corrupted Video Files

This is where things got frustrating.

