What I Learned

If there's one thing this experience taught me, it's that backups are not optional.

As creators, we spend so much time shooting, editing, and perfecting our work that it's easy to forget how fragile digital files can be.

A single wrong click nearly cost me 100GB of footage.

Thankfully, I got lucky.

Follow the 3-2-1 Backup Rule

Professional creators should always try to maintain:

3 copies of their data
2 different storage devices
1 off-site or cloud backup
Stop Using the Drive Immediately

The faster you stop using the drive after deletion, the higher your chances of successful recovery.

Recover First, Repair Later

Don't start experimenting with repair tools before recovering the files.

Always:

Recover the files first
Save them to a different drive
Then repair any corrupted files
